text:
Lafayette Avenue, east from Longwood Avenue, across the bridge over the New York, New Haven and Hartford Railroad tracks. Beyond the bridge is the plant of the American Bank Note Company, at Tiffany Street. The old house on the right is No. 1061 Longwood Avenue. View 2 shows the same area at a later date.

P. L. Sperr

View 1: July 4, 1928
View 2: September 9, 1938
